    {
      "id": "KsdJl-yOUqNryjNtqXQgB",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -7502.447995200659,
      "y": -3621.2384104861057,
      "width": 1906.699951171875,
      "height": 770,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffd8a8",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0z",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 903888575,
      "version": 1664,
      "versionNonce": 503460799,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1780669067514,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Functional Requirements\n\n\n- Engineer must be able to ship their code\n- Quality gateway: testing, linting, test coverage, SLOs for rollout\n- Security gateway: image scanning, immutable images, non-bypassable guardrails\n (compliance)\n- Build system: build code & generate artifacts. Build image only once\n- Deploy system: deploy code\n\n- Hot-fix deployments\n- Safe rollout, progressive rollout & canary\n- Automatic rollback\n- Multi-region deployments\n- Autoscaling of the platform, and absorb massive spikes\n- Observability and metrics of the platform.\n- Self remediation. If the pipelines are too slow, how observe and self-remediate. Survive production chaos\n- Guarantee non-bypassable guardrails\n- Network isolation, it must be able to deploy in other private k8s cluster (no public ips), draw security network boundaries, isolate team A from team B\n- RBAC\n- 3 layer approach: Interface plane, Control plane (validate schema & generate templates, handle persistent state management), Data plane\n",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Functional Requirements\n\n\n- Engineer must be able to ship their code\n- Quality gateway: testing, linting, test coverage, SLOs for rollout\n- Security gateway: image scanning, immutable images, non-bypassable guardrails\n (compliance)\n- Build system: build code & generate artifacts. Build image only once\n- Deploy system: deploy code\n\n- Hot-fix deployments\n- Safe rollout, progressive rollout & canary\n- Automatic rollback\n- Multi-region deployments\n- Autoscaling of the platform, and absorb massive spikes\n- Observability and metrics of the platform.\n- Self remediation. If the pipelines are too slow, how observe and self-remediate. Survive production chaos\n- Guarantee non-bypassable guardrails\n- Network isolation, it must be able to deploy in other private k8s cluster (no public ips), draw security network boundaries, isolate team A from team B\n- RBAC\n- 3 layer approach: Interface plane, Control plane (validate schema & generate templates, handle persistent state management), Data plane\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
